The paper deals with image super-resolution, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves Bayesian modeling techniques (cs.IT) and sparse modeling of natural images (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of Markov Random Fields (MRF) (cs.MM) and empirical Bayesian estimation scheme (cs.SI).
